CHAT.comment: MO starts out by telling IN about a letter that she has received from her aunt, whom IN and MO were going to go visit. HY plays with trucks and cars for most of the visit, with MO trying to get him to look at books towards the end.

HY is confused with what to call IN now, after seeing a "foreigner" (Caucasian woman with blonde hair) on TV and calling her "a1+yi2" (auntie, what he calls IN) and being corrected by MO. In response, he now starts calling IN "wai4+guo2+ren2" (foreigner) and again gets corrected. In this visit there is also an interesting overextension with the verb "tao1".
